('P9b', '<p><h4><b>Activity Construction Prompt 3:</h4> <br>Decide what multiple condition sets to show students through visualization<br><br> Guidelines:</b> <ul> <li>You need to play the visualization to: <br>1. Show both representations (graph/equation/model) together on-screen<br>2. Decide which feature you want to change first in representation 1 and show its effect on the corresponding feature in representation 2<br>3. Choose 1 more feature in representation 1 whose effect you want to show on the corresponding feature in representation 2<br>4. If there are multiple variable features to change then show effect of change of each feature individually.<br>5. Keep the effect of combination of the various variables together for the student activity later.<br>6. If you have a video/animation, note the timestamps for the video/animation or the code line in the programe where you need to pause to show each condition.<br></p>', 'CSE', '<p>For Topic = Pointers<br>I will relate between the code segment on Pointer Arithmetic & the  illustration of pointer variables insdie the computer when:<br>(i) Prefix operator codeline is executed<br>(ii) Postfix operator codeline is executed</p>', 1, 'Enter the multiple condition sets you will show students', 0, '', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 'Specify visualization feature to be used', '8', '##Play button##Pause button##Slider bars##Radio Buttons##Input Box##Checkboxes##Onscreen Labels/Text explanations##Others', 0, NULL, NULL, '1', 'Enter any other feature to be used:', '8', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, 55),
('P9b', '<p><h4><b>Activity Construction Prompt 3:</h4> <br>Decide what multiple condition sets to show students through visualization<br><br> Guidelines:</b> <ul> <li>You need to play the visualization to: <br>1. Show both representations (graph/equation/model) together on-screen<br>2. Decide which feature you want to change first in representation 1 and show its effect on the corresponding feature in representation 2<br>3. Choose 1 more feature in representation 1 whose effect you want to show on the corresponding feature in representation 2<br>4. If there are multiple variable features to change then show effect of change of each feature individually.<br>5. Keep the effect of combination of the various variables together for the student activity later.<br>6. If you have a video/animation, note the timestamps for the video/animation or the code line in the programe where you need to pause to show each condition.<br></p>', 'EE', '<p>1] Multiple Condition Sets to show:<br>For topic = Digital Modulation,  I will relate between the different points in the digital and analog signals.<br>I will show the AM and FM waveforms when signal is :<br>(i) all zeros<br>(ii) all ones.<br>Ans. 2] Visualization feature (s) to be used = Input boxes\"</p>', 1, 'Enter the multiple condition sets you will show students', 0, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', 'Specify visualization feature to be used', '8', '##Play button##Pause button##Slider bars##Radio Buttons##Input Box##Checkboxes##Onscreen Labels/Text explanations##Others##', 0, NULL, NULL, '1', 'Enter any other feature to be used:', '8', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, 56),
('P11b', '<p><b>Activity Construction Prompt 4: Frame parent activity question</b><br><br><b>Guidelines:</b><br>Frame a parent activity question on multiple representation whose solution can be shown through the visualization i.e.<br>Choose those parameters in one representation (e.g. graph or equation or model) whose values you can change visually through check boxes or slider bars or video capture etc.<br>Solving the parent activity question should ideally require students to do both :<br><ul><li>Relate corresponding parts in the 2 representations</li><li>Translate 1 representation into the other.</li></ul></p>', 'CSE', '<p>Parent Question : Binary Search Tree can have 2 representations:<br> tree form with nodes & doubly-liked list form. <br>Draw the linked list form after deleting a specified node.</p>', 1, 'Enter your parent activity question to solve with visualization:', 0, NULL, '1', 'Choose the extent of Prediction activity you want your students to do :', '2', '##Identifying the causal relationship between variables + conceptualize the working model##Only identifying the causal relationship between variables', '0', '', '0', NULL, '0', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, 57),
('P11b', '<p><b>Activity Construction Prompt 4: Frame parent activity question</b><br><br><b>Guidelines:</b><br>Frame a parent activity question on multiple representation whose solution can be shown through the visualization i.e.<br>Choose those parameters in one representation (e.g. graph or equation or model) whose values you can change visually through check boxes or slider bars or video capture etc.<br>Solving the parent activity question should ideally require students to do both :<br><ul><li>Relate corresponding parts in the 2 representations</li><li>Translate 1 representation into the other.</li></ul></p>', 'EE', '<p>Topic = Signal Transformation<br>Parent question to solve with visualization is:<br>A continuous time signal x (t) is shown on screen. Sketch the signal x(4 -t/2) and write mathematical expression after each transformation.</p>', 1, 'Enter your parent activity question to solve with visualization:', 0, NULL, '1', 'Choose the extent of Prediction activity you want your students to do :', '2', '##Identifying the causal relationship between variables + conceptualize the working model##Only identifying the causal relationship between variables', '0', NULL, '0', NULL, '0', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, 58);

